==================================
        Optional Class 
==================================

=> To overcome all of these nullpointerexception error we have a solution that introduced in java 1.8v.......
=> Optional class is used to avoid NullPointerExceptions in the program...........


Q. What is NullPointerException( NPE )?

Ans. When we perform some operation on null value then we will get NullPointerException..

   String s = null;
   s.length ();//NPE

==> To avoid NullPointerException we have to implement null check before performing operation on the object like below ...

   String s = null;
   if(s!= null){

    system.out.println(s.length());
   }

Note: In project there is no guarantee that every programmer will implement null checks.if anybody forget to implement null check then program will run into NullPointerException .

To avoid this problem we need to use Optional class like below 


User.java
=========
package OptionalClassConcept;

import java.util.Optional;

public class User {

public Optional<String> getUsername(Integer id){
	
	String name = null;
	if(id == 100) {
		
		name = "Raju";
	}else if(id == 101) {
		
		name = "Ranu";
	}else if(id == 103) {
		
		name = "Rani";
	}
	
	return Optional.ofNullable(name);
    }
}


